President Obama has issued a proclamation recognizing Public Service Recognition Week, which honors the individuals who dedicate their lives to serving the country. He acknowledges the hard work and sacrifice of public servants, including civil servants, scientists, teachers, social workers, and first responders. Despite challenges such as pay freezes and budget cuts, these leaders continue to make a difference and uphold the values that bind the nation together. The President emphasizes the importance of investing in the next generation of civil servants and creating an environment where all employees feel valued and included. He calls upon all Americans to show gratitude and appreciation for the work of public servants during this week.